 ODM leader Raila Odinga will embark on a Mt.Kenya tour on Thursday, beginning his day in Nyeri County where he is expected to meet local leaders.  On Friday, he will visit Kieni to popularise the ‘Azimio La Umoja’ rallying call, and on Saturday, he will hold rallies in within Nyeri county before capping it with a major rally in Nyeri Town.  Deputy President William, on the other hand, will be in Nakuru on Thursday, beginning his tour with a meeting at the Mwisho Wa Lami in Njoro Sub County.  He will then proceed to Mau Narok, Mauche, Kihingo, Egerton and Njoro Posta, all in Njoro sub-county for similar meetings.  The second-in-command will then proceed to Molo and Kuresoi North sub-counties with stop overs in Elburgon, Molo Town, Muchorwe and Seguton respectively.  He will cap his Thursday itinerary with three other meetings in Kuresoi south, making stopovers in Keringet, Olenguruone, and  Kiptagich.